Go home.

16:29.620 --> 16:30.644
Wipe Dad's gun off

16:30.690 --> 16:31.782
and put it back
where you found it.

16:31.820 --> 16:32.889
Don't say anything to Mom.

16:32.920 --> 16:34.649
Don't say anything to anyone.

16:34.690 --> 16:36.157
Forget this happened.

16:37.290 --> 16:38.325
Understood?

16:40.630 --> 16:41.790
What are you gonna do?

16:44.770 --> 16:46.294
I'll take care of this.

16:48.200 --> 16:49.792
Don't say another word.

16:49.840 --> 16:51.159
Just go.

16:53.240 --> 16:57.074
* Preacher sighs

16:59.880 --> 17:03.441
* Pack your things

17:03.490 --> 17:05.845
ROBBY: You ever lose sleep
at night 'cause of what we did
back then?

17:07.160 --> 17:09.219
Some nights.

17:09.260 --> 17:11.182
Not many.

17:11.230 --> 17:13.152
Ever wish you could
take it back?

17:13.200 --> 17:15.623
This man killed our father.

17:15.660 --> 17:18.060
Then stood at his wake
and lied to our faces.

17:18.100 --> 17:20.295
He was a disgrace
to the badge he wore.

17:20.340 --> 17:21.591
The one you were
going to wear.

17:21.640 --> 17:22.891
The one I wear
every day.

17:24.110 --> 17:27.637
No, this scumbag
got everything that
was coming to him.

17:27.680 --> 17:29.329
So, no.

17:29.380 --> 17:30.677
I wouldn't take it back.

17:31.810 --> 17:32.799
You?

17:33.550 --> 17:35.279
* Ohh

17:37.050 --> 17:38.449
Ah, we better get going.

17:39.920 --> 17:41.353
Night watchman will be
coming soon.

17:41.390 --> 17:44.723
* Don't be scared

17:46.990 --> 17:50.869
* I'm still here

17:53.900 --> 17:58.837
* No more time

18:00.040 --> 18:04.579
* For crying, dear *

18:04.610 --> 18:07.374
**

18:25.800 --> 18:28.234
(TIRES SCREECH, ENGINE REVS)

18:28.270 --> 18:30.033
**

18:33.740 --> 18:37.244
Listen, Robby, look, I...
I should say, uh...

18:37.280 --> 18:38.907
Should say
that I'm sorry.

18:38.950 --> 18:40.269
About what?

18:40.320 --> 18:42.117
What I said earlier,
back at the house.

18:42.150 --> 18:44.880
Look, I-I've been
hard on you.

18:44.920 --> 18:47.252
I left this place behind,
and you stayed,
and that was...

18:48.060 --> 18:49.084
That was
the harder choice,

18:49.120 --> 18:50.485
and I should give you
credit for it.

18:51.660 --> 18:53.196
For everything.
All your success.

18:53.230 --> 18:55.118
Work, everything.

18:55.960 --> 18:57.894
(LID RATrLES, CLOSES)

18:57.930 --> 18:59.192
Thank you, Don.

18:59.230 --> 19:00.629
Look, I was a prick
when we were younger,

19:00.670 --> 19:03.662
and I'm the reason
why we're taking care
of this now, but...

19:03.710 --> 19:04.904
You had my back
that night.

19:04.940 --> 19:06.168
Of course I did.

19:08.310 --> 19:09.379
You're my brother.

19:12.610 --> 19:14.248
I never thanked you.

19:14.280 --> 19:18.341
**

19:18.390 --> 19:20.085
Look, you saved me.

19:20.120 --> 19:22.384
That night, everything
in my life changed.

19:25.160 --> 19:26.582
Well, you might've noticed,

19:26.630 --> 19:28.029
it wasn't exactly
the same for me, either.

19:28.930 --> 19:30.522
Looks like you're doing
pretty good now.

19:31.400 --> 19:33.368
Hey, maybe you could take me
by this garage

19:33.400 --> 19:34.492
while I'm still in town?

19:36.370 --> 19:37.632
Yeah, cool.

19:37.670 --> 19:39.308
(ENGINE REWING)
I'd like that.

19:39.340 --> 19:41.171
(TIRES SCREECHING)

19:41.210 --> 19:43.132
**

19:45.980 --> 19:48.016
Robby, tell me
that was random.

19:48.050 --> 19:50.439
Okay, I can explain.

19:50.490 --> 19:52.742
**

19:56.290 --> 19:58.781
ROBBY:
My garage isn't doing as well
as I might have let Mom think.

19:58.830 --> 20:00.183
Oh, you don't say?

20:00.230 --> 20:02.551
I was losing money,
so I hired a bunch of guys.

20:02.600 --> 20:03.862
I thought they were
stand-up guys.

20:03.900 --> 20:07.461
And, uh... Anyway,
I needed some fast cash.

20:07.500 --> 20:10.264
Couldn't stand for
another failure, Donnie.

20:10.310 --> 20:12.505
Who'd you borrow money from?
Definitely not the banks.

20:12.540 --> 20:14.269
Those places, you walk in,
they don't even look at you...

20:14.310 --> 20:15.402
Robby.

20:15.440 --> 20:17.499
I borrowed it
from a local guy.

20:17.550 --> 20:19.609
What do you mean,
a connected
kind of local guy?

20:23.250 --> 20:25.741
Yeah, the Albanian type.

20:25.790 --> 20:27.314
The mob?
The Albanian mob?

20:29.220 --> 20:30.619
How much money
did you borrow?

20:31.230 --> 20:32.219
50K.

20:33.260 --> 20:35.125
It was 30% vig on it.

20:35.160 --> 20:36.559
And that was
like six months ago.
(LAUGHS)

20:36.600 --> 20:41.196
So it's closer
to 150K now, so...

20:41.240 --> 20:44.107
That's why they took the car,
you know, as collateral.

20:46.470 --> 20:48.779
I had to try something.
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

20:48.810 --> 20:50.607
Is there anything else
you're not telling me?

20:50.650 --> 20:52.140
No, I swear.

20:52.180 --> 20:53.169
That's it.

20:54.080 --> 20:56.173
Hey, man.
It's for you.

21:00.460 --> 21:02.416
Who is this?
MAN: We have your car.

21:02.460 --> 21:04.325
And the cargo in the trunk.

21:04.360 --> 21:06.328
Jakov Mitko wants
to see you both.

21:06.360 --> 21:07.452
Who's Jakov Mitko?

21:08.060 --> 21:09.254
Your brother knows.

21:09.300 --> 21:11.063
He knows where, too.

21:11.100 --> 21:12.499
Don't be late.
(CLICK)

21:12.530 --> 21:13.633
**

21:23.110 --> 21:25.476
You know the thing
about plants?

21:26.080 --> 21:28.275
They are obedient.

21:28.320 --> 21:30.379
A little love,
a little care,

21:30.420 --> 21:32.945
they do exactly
what they are supposed to.

21:32.990 --> 21:35.254
They grow.
They give back.

21:35.290 --> 21:37.178
Oxygen, flowers.

21:37.220 --> 21:39.825
They are uncomplicated.

21:39.860 --> 21:42.397
Anyone can respect that,
yes?

21:43.130 --> 21:45.997
You must be the brother
from D.C.

21:46.030 --> 21:48.669
Everyone thought
I was crazy
to loan money

21:48.700 --> 21:50.463
to a guy
whose brother was FBI.

21:50.510 --> 21:52.466
I said, "Wait and see."

21:52.510 --> 21:56.139
_ I don't think
In a million years
I could've seen this.

21:56.180 --> 21:57.545
Listen, Jakov,
I'm gonna get your money.

21:57.580 --> 21:58.774
Every last penny of it.

21:58.810 --> 22:00.675
This isn't about money
anymore.

22:00.720 --> 22:02.017
I don't understand this.

22:02.050 --> 22:03.278
He has the car.

22:03.320 --> 22:04.719
That's what this is about.

22:05.620 --> 22:06.689
Ah.

22:09.690 --> 22:11.021
Voila.

22:14.800 --> 22:18.964
I don't know
who Detective 4818

22:19.000 --> 22:22.492
of the Detroit
Police Department was,

22:22.540 --> 22:25.100
but he's seen better days.

22:25.140 --> 22:26.664
Just tell us
what you want.

22:26.710 --> 22:29.929
I was going to burn
down your garage,

22:29.980 --> 22:31.174
just to prove I could.

22:31.210 --> 22:33.144
I thought that was
your only asset.

22:33.180 --> 22:34.943
But now that
your brother is here,

22:34.980 --> 22:36.470
I know I was wrong.

22:36.520 --> 22:37.839
An FBI agent?

22:37.890 --> 22:39.482
Now that's
a whole other thing.

22:41.360 --> 22:45.456
At the field Office of the FBI
here in Detroit,

22:45.490 --> 22:48.323
there is a room called
Department 12.

22:48.360 --> 22:49.691
I have never seen it.

22:49.730 --> 22:51.789
I am told it is mostly
computers.

22:51.830 --> 22:56.062
Computers that an agent
like yourself can access.

22:56.100 --> 23:01.128
Go to that room, and bring me
back a file labeled "432."

23:01.180 --> 23:02.533
What is it?

23:02.580 --> 23:05.344
Have that file back here
by 5:00 pm. today.

23:06.380 --> 23:07.916
If you do that,

23:09.520 --> 23:13.752
I will give you back the car
and everything that's in it.

23:13.790 --> 23:15.451
And as an added incentive,

23:15.490 --> 23:18.220
I will wipe your
brother's debt clean.

23:20.530 --> 23:21.656
Hey.

23:22.800 --> 23:24.825
I know
what you're gonna say.

23:24.870 --> 23:26.269
**

23:30.240 --> 23:31.559
Okay, fine,
I deserved that.

23:31.610 --> 23:33.407
You know what
Department 12
is, Robby?

23:33.440 --> 23:36.671
It's the office UCs file
their sealed reports to.

23:36.710 --> 23:39.178
Now, in case
you forgot watching
Miami Vice as kids,

23:39.210 --> 23:40.711
UC stands
for "undercover."

23:40.750 --> 23:43.241
So, whoever's name's in there
is gonna get killed

23:43.280 --> 23:45.248
'cause I gotta run
that psycho's little errand.

23:45.290 --> 23:46.848
I'm not an idiot.

23:46.890 --> 23:47.879
I'm not an idiot!

23:49.920 --> 23:51.581
Don't treat me like one!

23:51.630 --> 23:54.292
**

23:54.330 --> 23:56.457
And you're not gonna do
what he's asking you to do!

23:57.160 --> 23:58.388
It'll destroy you.

23:58.430 --> 24:00.295
Yeah, and if I don't,

24:00.330 --> 24:02.662
he's gonna take those remains
and he's gonna turn them in,

24:02.700 --> 24:04.236
and it's gonna destroy
both of us.

24:04.270 --> 24:05.737
I'll take
full responsibility.

24:05.770 --> 24:07.704
We both know I can't
let you do that, okay?

24:07.740 --> 24:09.105
I killed that guy.

24:09.140 --> 24:10.209
Donnie, Donnie...

24:10.240 --> 24:11.241
No, this is my mess.

24:12.750 --> 24:13.910
You still don't get it.

24:14.880 --> 24:16.313
It isn't only your mess.

24:17.320 --> 24:19.185
**

24:23.260 --> 24:24.579
ROBBY: It was just me
and the body.

24:26.360 --> 24:28.123
You're shocked what your brain
can come up with

24:28.160 --> 24:29.718
when you're on
autopilot like that.

24:35.500 --> 24:37.365
(SHOVEL SCRAPING)

24:39.040 --> 24:42.908
I thought a lot about
how most people's lives hinge
on a few key moments.

24:43.850 --> 24:45.203
(MARKIN MOANS)

24:47.110 --> 24:48.771
(MARKIN COUGHS)

24:48.820 --> 24:50.981
**

24:53.350 --> 24:55.352
I think mine only had
one moment,

24:56.360 --> 24:57.952
and then it was over.

24:57.990 --> 25:00.220
**

25:04.600 --> 25:05.669
(RASPING) Robby...

25:07.770 --> 25:08.839
Please...

25:10.040 --> 25:11.598
I know you had
Dad killed, Tommy.

25:13.010 --> 25:13.999
Donnie told me the truth.

25:15.210 --> 25:16.632
Letting me die...

25:18.810 --> 25:20.368
Won't make us even...

25:20.410 --> 25:22.776
**

25:25.220 --> 25:26.949
(CRYING)

25:30.020 --> 25:31.624
You took my father from me.

25:34.200 --> 25:35.224
How could you?

25:35.260 --> 25:37.251
It... It was...

25:39.900 --> 25:41.060
Business...

25:42.800 --> 25:47.169
In that moment, I suddenly
had this clear thought.

25:47.210 --> 25:50.509
And I knew I was
the only person that
could protect you, Don.

25:50.540 --> 25:52.178
From Tommy Markin,

25:52.210 --> 25:54.212
and anyone else like him
who might come along.

25:56.280 --> 25:57.816
I had no choice...

25:58.650 --> 26:00.345
(SHOVEL THUDS)

26:00.390 --> 26:03.985
I finished what you started.
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

26:04.030 --> 26:05.349
I did it for you.

26:06.260 --> 26:07.818
For me.

26:07.860 --> 26:09.191
And for Daddy.

26:10.600 --> 26:13.467
In the end, all I was
thinking about was you.

26:15.600 --> 26:17.568
I was protecting
your future.

26:17.610 --> 26:20.909
Yeah, but why?
Why didn't you tell me?

26:20.940 --> 26:23.841
What... W-Why keep this
a secret all these years?

26:25.110 --> 26:27.670
I did that
to protect you, too.

26:27.720 --> 26:30.917
Whatever that night had done
to you, it was driving you.

26:32.190 --> 26:33.418
I carried the weight.

26:33.450 --> 26:35.088
I never regretted it.

26:36.960 --> 26:39.224
Because it did exactly
what I thought it would do.

26:39.260 --> 26:40.454
And what's that?

26:42.200 --> 26:43.929
It made you the person
that you are today.

26:45.400 --> 26:46.799
So it's not your mess.

26:48.070 --> 26:49.298
It's my mess, brother.

26:51.440 --> 26:52.805
I'll turn myself in.

26:54.210 --> 26:55.279
No.

26:57.310 --> 26:58.641
We turn ourselves in.

27:00.350 --> 27:02.409
I left you alone once
to clean up a mess.

27:03.990 --> 27:05.787
I'm not gonna leave you
alone again.

27:06.420 --> 27:08.354
**

27:12.990 --> 27:14.298
And s-so we...

27:15.900 --> 27:17.629
Killed the man
who killed our father.

27:17.670 --> 27:19.228
I pulled the trigger,
yeah".

27:19.270 --> 27:21.431
And to protect me,
my brother did the rest.

27:22.670 --> 27:24.900
But we each had
a hand in it.

27:24.940 --> 27:27.204
Look, we know
where the body is.
We can take you to it.

27:27.240 --> 27:29.879
But_ because of
my involvement,

27:29.910 --> 27:31.047
I have to recuse myself

27:31.080 --> 27:32.877
from any part of the
rest of this case.

27:32.910 --> 27:34.309
That's why I called you.

27:35.180 --> 27:36.408
I knew you would help.

27:36.450 --> 27:38.418
I... I knew you would do
the right thing.

27:38.450 --> 27:39.940
Ressler, I...

27:42.460 --> 27:44.257
I'm not sure what
I'm supposed to say.

27:44.290 --> 27:46.588
Well, say you agree
with me about how
we should handle this.

27:46.630 --> 27:49.098
I mean,
we arrest those bastards
who took the car

27:49.130 --> 27:53.123
for theft, for extortion,
for all the other poison
they pump into the city.

27:53.170 --> 27:55.638
**

27:55.670 --> 27:56.932
And then after that,

27:58.810 --> 28:00.732
my brother and I come clean
about what we've done.

28:01.540 --> 28:03.371
I don't know
that I do agree.

28:03.410 --> 28:04.707
After the story
you told me,

28:04.750 --> 28:06.342
after what you've
been through,
both of you...

28:06.380 --> 28:08.075
No, we have to do
the right thing.

28:08.120 --> 28:09.269
It's important.

28:10.650 --> 28:13.380
Of course, yes,
I will help you.

28:13.420 --> 28:15.149
I just want to make sure
you're prepared

28:15.190 --> 28:16.657
to face the consequences

28:16.690 --> 28:20.148
when the FBI gets
their hands on that
vehicle and that body.

28:20.190 --> 28:23.125
Because if we go in
and arrest those people,
eventually,

28:23.160 --> 28:24.798
the FBI's gonna
open up that trunk.

28:24.830 --> 28:26.559
And find Tommy Markin.
I know.

28:28.070 --> 28:30.766
Are you really okay
with dealing with the
consequences of that?

28:32.140 --> 28:34.574
I've been running from this
my whole life.

28:34.610 --> 28:37.477
I need it to be done.
We both need it to be done.

28:37.510 --> 28:39.876
**

28:46.350 --> 28:48.215
(BUTTON CLICKS)
Yeah, this is Agent Keen.

28:48.260 --> 28:50.182
Can I get SAC Patel
in here, please?

28:51.060 --> 28:52.357
Thank you.

28:53.060 --> 28:54.596
(RECEIVER CLATrERS)

28:54.630 --> 28:57.190
I need someone local _
to run pOint With me on this.

28:58.230 --> 28:59.959
We should go over
what the plan is.

29:00.000 --> 29:01.331
(SIGHS)

29:02.270 --> 29:03.760
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLARES)

29:03.810 --> 29:06.529
**

29:17.350 --> 29:19.386
We'll be around the corner,
two blocks away.

29:19.420 --> 29:21.411
Twelve-second
response time,
I'd guess.

29:21.460 --> 29:23.109
Wanna go over/under
on that?

29:24.290 --> 29:25.757
It's gonna be dangerous.

29:25.790 --> 29:27.223
When is it not?

29:27.260 --> 29:29.228
You know, I can still talk
to Patel, call it off.

29:29.260 --> 29:30.591
I have the authority...

29:30.630 --> 29:31.790
You know, Keen...

29:33.370 --> 29:34.928
I didn't like you
when we first met.

29:36.470 --> 29:37.960
I was wrong.
You're a good agent.

29:38.010 --> 29:39.739
You're the kind
of agent that

29:39.770 --> 29:41.306
people join the FBI
to try to become.

29:42.740 --> 29:45.538
But you're also
a good person.

29:45.580 --> 29:46.979
Much better person
than I am.

29:47.980 --> 29:49.709
So, whatever happens
out there today,

29:49.750 --> 29:52.583
the Task Force is gonna be
in good hands with you.

29:52.620 --> 29:55.259
**

30:00.230 --> 30:01.219
You all right?

30:03.460 --> 30:04.768
This is gonna kill Mom.

30:06.700 --> 30:07.860
Tell me again.

30:09.940 --> 30:11.305
We're doing the right thing?

30:12.010 --> 30:14.433
Yeah, Robby. We are.

30:14.480 --> 30:15.799
We're doing the right thing.

30:15.840 --> 30:17.842
**

30:24.790 --> 30:26.018
(ENGINE SHUTS OFF)

30:26.050 --> 30:27.813
**

30:40.200 --> 30:43.658
I would be lying ifI said
I wasn't surprised

30:43.700 --> 30:45.338
that you went through
with it.

30:46.540 --> 30:47.700
File 432.

30:49.740 --> 30:51.708
You don't care
who's on it?

30:51.750 --> 30:52.978
That's not my business.

30:54.220 --> 30:56.472
Your brother
is sweating.

30:56.520 --> 30:58.886
And he looks nervous.

30:58.920 --> 31:01.411
It's because
it's humid in here
and he loves his car.

31:01.460 --> 31:03.280
How about we see it?

31:03.320 --> 31:06.528
MITKO: Okay.
Let us go and see it.

31:06.990 --> 31:09.049
**

31:10.660 --> 31:11.797
One more thing
before we trade.

31:11.830 --> 31:13.798
What do you want?
A plant?

31:13.830 --> 31:16.731
A nice orchid to go?
(CHUCKLES)

31:16.770 --> 31:19.000
My brother
checks out the car
for confirmation.

31:21.040 --> 31:22.029
Come on, Robby, do it.

31:23.380 --> 31:25.200
**

31:30.480 --> 31:32.311
(COUGHS)

31:34.220 --> 31:35.687
My file.

31:35.720 --> 31:37.551
**

31:39.330 --> 31:40.581
Looks like we're finished.

31:43.030 --> 31:45.760
Ressler, you're sure
this is what you want?

31:45.800 --> 31:51.033
Actually, I think I might
have a few more projects
I need your help with.

31:51.070 --> 31:52.935
No, this was
a one-time deal.

31:52.970 --> 31:54.369
Or it wasn't.

31:54.410 --> 31:57.948
I still have the car
and my file.

31:57.980 --> 31:59.072
You sure about that?

32:00.050 --> 32:01.517
The drive is blank.
It's a fake!

32:01.550 --> 32:03.177
We're a go!
G0, 90, 90, 90!

32:03.220 --> 32:04.778
(GRU NTS)

32:07.620 --> 32:09.759
FBI! Hands!
On the ground!

32:16.630 --> 32:18.268
East entrance
to the greenhouse!
Let's move!

32:18.300 --> 32:19.392
MITKO: Tradhtar!

32:19.430 --> 32:22.433
I'll grind your guts
to fertilizer!

32:22.470 --> 32:23.539
LIZ: Hey, you!

32:23.570 --> 32:25.128
**

32:31.980 --> 32:33.948
Everyone okay back here?

32:33.980 --> 32:36.244
_Yeah. Your friend
just saved my life.

32:36.880 --> 32:38.086
I wouldn't say that.

32:39.650 --> 32:41.459
I don't think
I saved anyone.

32:41.490 --> 32:43.754
**

32:47.760 --> 32:49.819
**

33:02.010 --> 33:04.069
PRIEST: Wait for the Lord
with courage.

33:04.110 --> 33:07.102
Be stouthearted
and wait for the Lord.

