And now, I've been
told Detective Ressler's
eldest son,

33:12.220 --> 33:14.950
Robert, would like
to say a few words.

33:14.990 --> 33:17.288
* I see problems down the line

33:19.690 --> 33:22.124
* I know they're not mine

33:27.830 --> 33:30.139
* Don't wash the dirt
off of your hands

33:32.670 --> 33:35.776
* Doing the same mistake twice

33:35.810 --> 33:38.199
* Making the same
mistake twice

33:40.650 --> 33:43.312
* Come on over

33:43.350 --> 33:46.842
* Don't be so caught up

33:46.890 --> 33:50.519
* It's not about compromising

33:50.560 --> 33:52.152
I know everyone here
knew my dad.

33:53.830 --> 33:56.424
Had some special version
of him to hold on to.

33:58.230 --> 34:00.494
What a good guy he was.

34:00.530 --> 34:01.792
What a good cop.

34:03.670 --> 34:05.035
I kinda wish I had that.

34:06.740 --> 34:08.207
Truth is,
I didn't really know him.

34:10.640 --> 34:12.039
My version of Dad

34:13.510 --> 34:15.375
is him stomping
into my school...

34:15.420 --> 34:16.842
(CHUCKLES)

34:16.880 --> 34:19.348
...fresh from patrol,
furious after I got caught

34:19.390 --> 34:20.414
putting cigarette butts

34:22.860 --> 34:25.784
* Don't wash the dirt
off of your hands

34:25.830 --> 34:27.559
Then he left too soon.

34:27.590 --> 34:29.490
* Doing the same mistake twice

34:29.530 --> 34:30.952
And what I have now,

34:31.000 --> 34:33.560
i-instead of a version
of him to hold onto...

34:35.240 --> 34:36.593
...is a path to follow.

34:38.070 --> 34:40.436
A path that shows me
how to grow up right,

34:42.580 --> 34:44.207
how to stay out of trouble,

34:46.780 --> 34:49.078
how to be good, like him.

34:49.120 --> 34:51.714
* I see problems down the line

34:51.750 --> 34:54.150
ROBBY: So, it started with me
only borrowing $50,000.

34:54.190 --> 34:55.987
But with interest,

34:56.020 --> 34:57.817
and the time
that had gone by,

34:57.860 --> 35:00.385
Mitko was demanding
that I pay back $150,000.

35:00.430 --> 35:02.091
That's when he came
after the car...

35:02.130 --> 35:05.019
I don't remember the number
on the badge,

35:05.070 --> 35:07.595
but it was
definitely a cop.

35:07.630 --> 35:10.758
The agent and his brother,
they knew about that.

35:10.800 --> 35:13.166
I would say more,
but I want to make
a deal first.

35:13.210 --> 35:14.404
Can you prove any of this?

35:14.440 --> 35:17.671
You go check out the trunk
of that car yourself.

35:18.510 --> 35:20.273
Agent Ressler...

35:21.450 --> 35:23.714
There has been an allegation
made against you

35:23.750 --> 35:26.412
and your brother by the man
we have in the other room.

35:26.450 --> 35:27.644
Yeah, we were
expecting that.

35:27.690 --> 35:29.214
It's a very serious
allegation.

35:34.600 --> 35:35.919
The thing about
this case is...

35:35.960 --> 35:37.928
**

35:40.330 --> 35:42.389
* Don't let the darkness
eat you up *

35:42.440 --> 35:43.737
Well, this is
interesting...

35:43.770 --> 35:45.829
**

35:47.340 --> 35:49.103
ROBBY: How is the body
just gone?

35:49.140 --> 35:51.074
I mean, Markin didn'tjust
get up and walk away.

35:53.510 --> 35:55.319
I think we're good.

35:55.350 --> 35:57.079
I mean, I don't know
exactly what happened,

35:57.120 --> 35:58.348
but I do have
some theories.

35:59.390 --> 36:01.278
I think someone was watching
over us, Robby.

36:02.460 --> 36:03.916
(SIGHS)

36:04.660 --> 36:06.628
Now what do we do?

36:06.660 --> 36:07.979
Well, I think we can
finally put this behind us

36:08.030 --> 36:09.099
and move on.

36:09.130 --> 36:11.621
(SIGHS)
I need a drink.

36:11.670 --> 36:13.228
(DOOR OPENS)

36:13.270 --> 36:15.135
**

36:15.640 --> 36:16.629
(DOOR CLOSES)

36:17.270 --> 36:18.760
Oh, hi, sweetie.

36:18.810 --> 36:20.437
Were you boys out
all night?

36:20.470 --> 36:21.505
Yeah, it was a...

36:22.010 --> 36:23.170
It was a long one.

36:24.580 --> 36:26.343
Well, did everything
work out Okay?

36:26.380 --> 36:27.449
What do you mean?

36:27.480 --> 36:30.176
Did you get Robby
out of the trouble he was in?

36:31.750 --> 36:33.240
I knew something was up.

36:33.290 --> 36:34.552
A mother knows.

36:36.160 --> 36:38.856
You here all of a sudden
on a "case."

36:38.890 --> 36:42.155
The case turned out
as well as pOSSIble.

36:42.200 --> 36:44.259
I'm pretty sure
Robby's gonna be Okay.

36:44.300 --> 36:45.562
Thank you, Donnie.

36:45.600 --> 36:48.535
Trouble or not,
your brother means well.

36:48.570 --> 36:51.334
He just gets himself
a bit lost sometimes.

36:51.370 --> 36:53.463
(SCOFFS)
I meant what I said
about your father

36:53.510 --> 36:54.977
being proud
of the both of you.

36:55.010 --> 36:56.409
You know why?

36:57.410 --> 36:59.071
Because you stick together.

37:00.080 --> 37:01.741
**

37:35.180 --> 37:37.216
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATION)

37:57.000 --> 37:58.558
ROBBY:
I couldn't do it.

37:58.610 --> 38:00.965
I couldn't just stand in front
of those people and say...

38:04.850 --> 38:05.976
What could I say?

38:07.410 --> 38:08.411
It's Okay.

38:09.580 --> 38:10.740
We got through it.

38:11.820 --> 38:13.412
(SNIFFS)
Tomorrow will be easier,

38:13.450 --> 38:14.883
and the day after that...

38:14.920 --> 38:16.478
Maybe you can do better
with this than I did.

38:20.660 --> 38:22.059
(SNIFFLES)

38:22.100 --> 38:23.249
This is Dad's?

38:25.000 --> 38:26.160
I can't be a cop.

38:28.270 --> 38:29.498
I'm nothing like him.

38:32.340 --> 38:34.001
I don't know
what I am anymore.

38:34.040 --> 38:36.338
**

39:00.670 --> 39:03.434
You heading back
to D.C., bud?
Yeah. Yeah.

39:03.470 --> 39:04.835
I'm sure the office
has missed me by now.

39:04.870 --> 39:06.269
(CHUCKLES)

39:07.740 --> 39:09.037
Mom's sure gonna miss you.

39:09.080 --> 39:10.138
Yeah.

39:10.180 --> 39:11.875
I'll call.
As often as I can.

39:13.180 --> 39:14.169
I have something for you.

39:15.020 --> 39:17.671
**

39:24.390 --> 39:25.618
Never thought
I'd see that again.

39:26.890 --> 39:28.721
I think it's your turn
to hang onto it a while.

39:33.100 --> 39:35.330
You don't think
Dad would've wanted the cop
in the family to have it?

39:35.370 --> 39:38.237
No, no.
I think he'd want you
to have it.

39:42.640 --> 39:43.834
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

39:46.010 --> 39:46.999
Bad time?

39:48.050 --> 39:49.517
No. No, come in.

39:55.660 --> 39:56.888
Did you do it
to protect me?

39:58.560 --> 40:00.050
You say that
like it's a bad thing.

40:01.190 --> 40:02.555
I'm not gonna ask you
how you did it.

40:02.600 --> 40:05.819
I won't ask what you did
with Markin's body or... Or...

40:05.870 --> 40:07.667
Or how you even
scrubbed that car clean,
but...

40:07.700 --> 40:09.463
I learned from the best.

40:09.500 --> 40:11.161
Look, I want to know...
I mean...

40:11.200 --> 40:13.407
Liz, I need to know...

40:13.440 --> 40:14.509
Why?

40:14.540 --> 40:17.031
**

40:17.080 --> 40:18.741
You were in trouble.
You needed help.

40:18.780 --> 40:20.998
No, y-y-you...
You risked everything.

40:21.050 --> 40:22.472
I mean, if you...
You'd have been caught...

40:22.520 --> 40:24.408
Yeah, but I wasn't.
Yeah, but you could've been.

40:25.790 --> 40:27.018
'Cause if that's
what you're doing,

40:27.050 --> 40:28.187
you're doing
a terrible job of it.

40:28.220 --> 40:29.551
I... I...

40:29.590 --> 40:31.729
I never would've
asked you to take such
a huge risk for me.

40:31.760 --> 40:33.819
You didn't ask.
Yeah, but you
did it anyway.

40:33.860 --> 40:35.748
It wasn't for you,
knucklehead.

40:35.800 --> 40:36.926
It was for me.

40:37.800 --> 40:39.097
For you?

40:39.130 --> 40:40.597
Look, if you wanna
ruin your life

40:40.630 --> 40:42.439
over something you did
a lifetime ago,

40:42.470 --> 40:44.131
when you were a teenager,
for God's sake,

40:44.170 --> 40:45.899
then someday, sure,
I'll let you.

40:46.740 --> 40:47.900
You'll let me.

40:47.940 --> 40:49.908
Yeah, you have my permission
to be a total dipstick.

40:49.940 --> 40:52.249
(CHUCKLES)
So, what am I?

40:52.280 --> 40:53.770
A dipstick
or a knucklehead?

40:53.810 --> 40:55.619
You're a knucklehead
and a dipstick,

40:55.650 --> 40:57.743
and you're someone
that I rely on,

40:57.780 --> 40:59.645
for, like, everything.

41:00.420 --> 41:01.910
We both know
that's not true.

41:04.660 --> 41:05.888
Have you looked at my life?

41:07.760 --> 41:09.751
I'm a widow
and a Single mom.

41:11.770 --> 41:14.091
A marionette

41:14.130 --> 41:17.031
with a high-functioning
sociopath pulling my strings.

41:18.810 --> 41:20.835
My grandfather tried
to murder my mother,

41:21.940 --> 41:25.671
and my mother is a legendarily
lethal Russian spy

41:26.950 --> 41:28.406
who moved in next door

41:28.450 --> 41:30.145
without even telling me
who She was.

41:30.180 --> 41:32.489
(SIGHS) I mean it.

41:32.520 --> 41:34.317
Have you looked at my life?

41:34.350 --> 41:36.318
I mean, really taken
a close look.

41:38.290 --> 41:41.020
Because it's like
I'm in the middle of a monsoon

41:41.060 --> 41:44.928
that's constantly threatening
to drown me in bad news.

41:46.330 --> 41:49.458
And somewhere in the middle
of that FEMA disaster

41:49.500 --> 41:50.489
of a life...

41:51.710 --> 41:57.000
(VOICE BREAKING) Somewhere
is just a tiny island of calm.

42:00.180 --> 42:01.613
And if that weren't there,

42:02.550 --> 42:04.347
I would be
swept out to sea.

42:04.380 --> 42:06.143
No, that's never
gonna happen...

42:06.190 --> 42:07.441
It would
if you weren't here.

42:07.490 --> 42:09.458
But I am.
And it won't.

42:09.490 --> 42:10.616
Come here.

42:12.060 --> 42:13.687
It's never gonna happen.

42:14.530 --> 42:16.293
Not on my watch.

42:16.330 --> 42:18.560
**

42:21.430 --> 42:23.864
**
